{{Youmay|the creation myth|the Mandalorian planet, [[Akaan]]}}
'''''Akaanati'kar'oya'''''&mdash;or the '''The War of Life and Death''', when translated from the [[Mando'a/Legends|''Mando'a'']] [[Language/Legends|language]] into [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]]&mdash;was a [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] creation tale told of in [[Mandalorian religion|Mandalorian mythology]].

In the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Mandalorian Crusaders]] and [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Neo-Crusaders]], the ''Akaanati'kar'oya'' was regarded literally, as a factual tale with events that truly happened in the ancient past.

However, as the Mandalorian culture continued to grow through the [[Standard century/Legends|centuries]], later Mandalorian [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] took to viewing the ''Akaanati'kar'oya'' and other myths like it allegorically, as parables not to be viewed in a literal sense, but to be interpreted for an underlying philosophical meaning.<ref name="TMPaC">{{InsiderCite|86|The Mandalorians: People and Culture}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The ''Akaanati'kar'oya'' was introduced in the [[Star Wars Insider]] article, ''[[The Mandalorians: People and Culture]]'', [[Author/Legends|authored]] by [[Karen Traviss]] and published in [[February]] [[2006]] as part of the magazine's [[Star Wars Insider 86|eighty-sixth]] issue.

